race.comment: Onto the first of three Group 1's, and what a cracking Coolmore Stud Stakes it is. TENTYRIS (3) has a real sense of timing about him. He drifted heavily here first up but still ran very well through the inferior ground before being heavily backed at Caulfield. The win there was outstanding, getting off heels and charging late in fast time. He can improve again and that will give the early favourite BEIWACHT (1) a real race. BEIWACHT is off five weeks coming back from the G1 Golden Rose where he was ultra-impressive winning by four lengths. He did have the pattern onside there but the form out of it has been outstanding and he'll be very hard to run down. BEADMAN (10) was unlucky in the G2 Roman Consul last time which has been a good guide to this race. Loved his recent jumpout down the straight. LEGACY BOUND (9) can run well at odds. He's crying out for 1200m and had things against in the G2 Danehill Stakes. SKYHOOK (5) has been good in the top Sydney leadups and has claims.
